About

Hello!

I'm a fourth-year student currently studying Computer Science at the University of California, Irvine.

I was born and raised in Southern California and am grateful to have grown up in such a warm, beautiful, and diverse place. Being raised in an untraditional Asian-American household with my mother being free-spirited & creative while my father was straightforward & practical, paved way for my multifaceted life path thus far.

Taking influence from both sides, I grew up loving music and fashion, in addition to technology. Prior to studying Computer Science, I dreamt of creating and self-expression with a career in fashion design. However, shortly after I discovered my passion for Computer Science while attending community college.

I still dream of creating however, now I do so as a Software Engineer with a passion for design and development.
